==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle French ''[[turbant]]'', from Italian ''[[turbante]]'', from Turkish ''[[tülbent]]'', from Persian ''[[dulband]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈtɜːrbən/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)bən|-ɜː(r)bən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Man's [[head-dress]] made by [[wind]]ing a [[length]] of [[cloth]] round the head.
# Woman's close-fitting [[hat]] with little or no [[brim]].

